#Text=Hijackers divert Libyan passenger jet to Malta
#Text=Friday , December 23 , 2016
#Text=Two hijackers seized an Afriqiyah Airways jet this morning , diverting it away from its domestic Libyan route to Malta .
#Text=The men surrendered to Maltese custody .
#Text=The aircraft involved , from file .
#Text=Image : Pedro Aragão ( CC BY-SA 3.0 ) .
#Text=Flight 209 , an Airbus A320 , was flying from Sabha to Tripoli .
#Text=Men identified as Suhaha Mussa and Ahmed Alid , armed with what appeared to be a grenade and two pistols , took control of the aircraft .
#Text=The airline said a proposal to land in Libya was rejected by the hijackers , who took the plane to nearby Malta owing to fuel limits .
#Text=After landing , the plane 's engines were not shut off for around ninety minutes .
#Text=Malta International Airport was closed after the arrival .
#Text=Negotiators and security forces met the plane , carrying 111 passengers and at least six crew , at the airport .
#Text=The hijackers released the passengers , one of whom was an infant , and most crewmembers before surrendering .
#Text=The hijacking appears to be in favour of Libya 's deceased , deposed former leader Muammar al-Gaddafi .
#Text=One hijacker waved a flag from the Gaddafi regime .
#Text=Libyan news station Channel TV said it spoke by phone to one hijacker , quoting him as saying " We took this measure to declare and promote our new party . "
#Text=Channel TV reported the man said he had formed a new group called al-Fateh al-Jadid , which means " The New al-Fateh " .

column1: #Text=Al-Gaddafi renamed September as al-Fateh in honour of his September 1969 coup ; al-Fateh came to be a term closely associated with him .
#Text=Malta International Airport , from file .
#Text=Image : William Shewring ( CC0 1.0 ) .
#Text=There were reports , including comments by a Libyan minister , the hijackers sought political asylum in Malta , something Maltese Prime Minister Joseph Muscat denied .
#Text=Muscat , who tweeted throughout today 's events , told a press conference the hostages would be questioned over several hours and then flown home by a replacement Afriqiyah Airways plane .

#Text=Libyan foreign minister Taher Siala , allied to the Government of National Accord , said the two hijackers intended to form a political party allied to Gaddafi , who died during a 2011 uprising .
#Text=Gaddafi used the same green flag as displayed by the hijackers from 1977 until his death .
#Text=One publication in Germany claimed the release of Saif al-Gaddafi was demanded .
#Text=The airline operates a twice-weekly Sabha-Tripoli route , on Fridays and Tuesdays .
#Text=Friday flights depart at 10:10am , and arrive seventy minutes later .
#Text=Passengers were being freed by 1:50pm in Malta ; at 3:50pm the hijackers surrendered .
#Text=Muscat spoke to Libyan Prime Minister Faez al-Serraj during the incident , according to Muscat 's communications chief Kurt Farrugia .
#Text=Negotiators reportedly included Libya 's transport minister , with Maltese efforts led by commander Jeffrey Curmi of the Armed Forces .
#Text=Thousands at an anti-Gaddafi rally in 2011 .
#Text=Image : ليبي صح ( CC0 1.0 ) .
#Text=The airport has reopened .
#Text=At least 44 flights were affected , with nine diverted to Sicily , Italy .
#Text=There were delays to twenty departures and fifteen arrivals .
#Text=Libya suffered a power vacuum since the 2011 fall of al-Gaddafi .
#Text=The nation , wealthy due to oil reserves , is split amongst competing governments and parliaments , controlled by rival militants .
#Text=The present internationally-recognised Government of National Accord is the result of United Nations negotiations .
#Text=The situation has led to the nation 's airports falling under the varying control of numerous armed groups .
#Text=Libya 's main airport was destroyed in 2014 when it caught fire during a battle for its control .
#Text=Libyan flights are banned from direct entry to European airspace .
#Text=" Every airport in Libya is poorly secured " , according to BBC correspondent Rana Jawad .
#Text=Malta has not seen a large-scale hijacking since November 1985 , when an EgyptAir plane was diverted there .
#Text=After a 24-hour standoff Maltese commandos burst on-board to rescue hostages from three hijackers .
#Text=The ensuing firefight left 62 dead .
